President Obama has announced the formation of a Presidential Delegation to attend the inauguration ceremony of President Ts. Elbegdorj of Mongolia. The delegation will be led by U.S. Ambassador to Mongolia, Piper Anne Wind Campbell, and will include Dr. Tomicah Tillemann, a Special Advisor for Civil Society and Emerging Democracies at the Department of State. The inauguration ceremony is set to take place on July 10, 2013.